SESSION.DESCRIPTION: 7/27/09 - This is a dummy session to update the TAPC_QTR_PRCS table. It will update the start and end time of the workflow. The update is done in a PRE SQL on the Target. The target connection is GDX. For errors, the Source connection is changed to an Oracle database in order to fail. The reason to fail is to be able to update the status. The previous session has to have the box to fail parent tasked UNCHECKED.

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This email was put in here instead of in the predecessor job, in case that predecessor moves or is removed. This workflow signals the end of heavy APC processing on the GDX box. This session sends out an email informing the users that APC is done on GDX.
TASKINSTANCE.NAME: s_m_Dummy_Email_GDX_is_avail_now

ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Email Subject
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE: APC is done working with GDX data - %d

ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Email Text
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE:
The quarterly APC process has completed the queries and pulling data on the GDX box, and is now working with flat files, and RPSDM data.
You can safely proceed with running processes on GDX without interferring with APC.
There are other processes later in the APC schedule that will use GDX data, but they are ancillary reports.
----- This email came from the %d system in workflow %w.
